![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b58e1036-830e-46dd-942c-c849f8a6b349)

@zeertzjq  Considering it's a static global variable. Including the header to multiple .c files would lead to linker error right? Global being defined twice?

Isn't just passing the necessary info better in that case as I've done with os_def? It's a pointer anyway doesn't really have any overhead.

